Dick O'Neill https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dick_O%27Neill 0 Richard Francis "Dick" O'Neill (August 29, 1928 – November 17, 1998) was an American stage, film and television character actor best known for playing Irish cops, fathers, judges and army generals. He began his acting career as an original company member of Arena Stage in Washington, D.C.
